As it was confirmed in previous experiments \cite{PathEnt2012}, the squeezing at the hybrid ring input is equivalent to a path entanglement of the output beams. Therefore, from a fundamental point of view, one must check whether the amount of bipartite path entanglement between the outputs of the entangling hybrid ring depends on the displacement power. To this end, we measure the negativity $N$.
For Gaussian states \cite{Negat2005, PathEnt2012}, it is defined as $N \,{\equiv}\, \max \left\{ 0, (1-\nu)/(2\nu) \right\}$, where
